---
import ChevronLeft from "@icons/ChevronLeft.astro";
import Layout from "@layouts/Layout.astro";
import P from "@components/P.astro";
---

<Layout title="Shlok Desai | SWE Intern @ Pyebook">
  <div class="flex justify-center max-w-7xl gap-x-16 mx-auto px-4">
    <div class="w-40 hidden xl:block">
      <button
        onclick="history.back();"
        class="inline-flex items-center gap-x-1 border-b border-gray9
              hover:border-gray11 hover:text-gray12 transition-colors w-fit
              tracking-wide font-light text-gray12 text-base"
      >
        <ChevronLeft size={16} />
         cd . .
      </button>
    </div>

    <div id="main" class="max-w-2xl w-full">
      <div class="flex items-center justify-between">
        <h1 class="text-gray12 tracking-wider">
          Software Engineer Intern{" "}
          <span class="text-gray11 font-light">@ Pyebook</span>
        </h1>

        <button
          onclick="history.back();"
          class="inline-flex items-center gap-x-1 border-b border-gray9
              hover:border-gray11 hover:text-gray12 transition-colors w-fit
              tracking-wide font-light text-gray12 text-base xl:hidden"
        >
          <ChevronLeft size={16} />
           cd . .
        </button>
      </div>

      <span class="text-gray11 font-light text-sm mt-4 block">
        Mumbai, India â€¢ 06/2021 - 08/2021
      </span>

      <P className="mt-8">
        Pyebook is a small edutech startup that teaches students to code using
        generative ebooks that adapt to their personal needs, pre-existing skill
        set and knowledge.
      </P>

      <P className="mt-4">
        It was founded by my mentor at the time, Rohan Arora. He taught me how
        to code, and helped me fall in love with the process. After learning the
        basics, I asked him to give me a internship at his company. This
        experience proved pivotal in my journey.
      </P>

      <P className="mt-8">Responsibilites:</P>

      <ul class="mt-4 list-disc text-gray11">
        <li>
          <P>
            Writing SQL queries and implementing JWT authentication in a REST
            API with a small developer team.
          </P>
        </li>
        <li>
          <P>
            Reducing average response times of Pyebook's REST API through the
            strategic implementation of MySQL indexes, query optimization, and
            server-level response caching. I managed to bring it down by ~20%.
          </P>
        </li>
        <li>
          <P>
            Leveraging React.js to design and develop UI components for the
            Pyebook web application. Build three new features and test them
            rigorously with unit tests written with Jest.
          </P>
        </li>
      </ul>

      <div class="pt-4"></div>
    </div>

    <div class="w-40 hidden xl:block"></div>
  </div>
</Layout>
